les below.  The shelves behind the bar hold nicknacks from the cocktail\\\'s heyday.  This is a place that takes its drinks seriously, it\\\'s nice that the cocktail thing is sort of still on an upswing in portland.  The drink menu has some interesting concoctions, shying away from vodka as is the new vogue -- of which i approve!  A good happy hour also includes some interesting takes on everyday items.  It\\\'s on the pricey side -- 8 to 9 bucks a drink versus Victory\\\'s 6.50 -- but the pours are good.  And at happy hour many of them go down to 5 bucks!  Staff is friendly and attentive, our server humored my attempts to discuss cocktails and their ingredients.  At first i was concerned that drinks were being poured with jiggers, but realized they were trying to do justice to each drink.  The speed may not keep up with demand on heavy nights, but i think a robust bartender is coming aboard.','2009-07-29 17:14:30',2,64),(341,'the atmosphere is slightly subdued, but the service is upbeat and welcoming.  you\\\'re dining in the front room of a remodeled craftsman beautifully restored.  adventurous northwest food combinations are great and can be shared happily.  great drinks, too.  will be going back, especially to give happy hour a shot.','2009-05-19 14:27:56',2,64),(344,'if you like beer, you\\\'ve probably already been here.  a constantly rotating selection of 20 beers on tap, and usually something on cask.  no food.  location great, but interior is ugly and you feel like you\\\'re in a cube being watched.  jeff, the owner, is a great guy with some good beer knowledge, though he won\\\'t try to impress you.  imperial pints.  4.50 each mostly.','2009-04-30 13:58:35',2,64),(345,'the benson.  a falling star.  this place used to be a staple for portlanders, recently it was just a comfortable place to escape to and have a good drink.  now, under poor management, it closes at random hours and the staff is going to shit.  at least there\\\'s always Arthur.  a man that kn