pecial occasion steelo.  wait for a good table if they ask.  def. recommend trying','2008-11-11 17:51:52',2,65),(129,'Adventurous chef with a changing menu of small and regular plates.  Had a wonderful evening here with lots of attention',NULL,2,65),(135,'best brew n view in town.  great staff, food, wine, movies',NULL,2,65),(145,'this is a great lunch spot!  it\'s like a soda fountain.  and as the name implies, they have daily special plates.  and it\'s cheap!  and they have a great n.a. drink menu, including my fav the egg cream.  great atmosphere.  can be a little hectic at lunch rush.  it\'s in rotation!','2009-03-11 17:31:49',2,65),(146,'This little unassuming cafe is the best breakfast spot in portland.  the staff is friendly, attentive and warm.  the normal breakfast fare is great, but the specials always have something a little special to offer, often with a southern bent.  don\'t spread the word.',NULL,2,65),(159,'My favorite place to stop on the way home for a glass of wine from a decent collection, and belgian-style mussels served with fries &amp; mayo ($7 app / $12 dinner.  Randy the bar-tender/owner is a delight.  closed Tuesdays like the rest of damn Foster.  what gives?','2008-03-25 22:21:02',6,65),(161,'Beast.  it speaks for itself.  this place is pretty damn good, but it\'s missing something.  can\'t quite put my finger on it.  maybe it\'s a little too forced and prescious.  in any case, the food is phenomenal and the service exquisite after dinner gets going.  they can be a little terse/overwhelemed feeling before the meal starts.  fixed price, common seating (just two giant tables).  6 courses.  wine pairing offered and highly recommended.  all told it was about $100 with a generous tip.  need to make a reservation for one of the 2 seatings a night.  worth it for the experience, but it\'s not a restaurant i would go to often','2008-10-10 12:37:08',2,65),(179,'what the space lacks in ambience is easily made up by the awesomeness that is their food,