Their breakfasts are super tasty!! ','2009-03-06 14:52:16',12,65),(305,'If you\'re in the mood for a yummy turkey burger, look no further. I had to keep checking that it was a turkey burger and not a hamburger. By far one of the best I\'ve had.','2009-03-06 15:55:39',7,65),(307,'Interesting sandwiches that leave you satisfied and filled. Get there pre-lunch hour to avoid lines. Don\'t waste your appetite on the chips. Go hun.gry','2009-03-06 16:10:39',7,65),(309,'Top notch hotel with a stated luxury feel. Particularly like the plush robes and prompt room service.','2009-03-06 16:14:03',7,65),(310,'This hotel transports you to the glamorous days of Hollywood. And it\'s all done just right. The bar reminds you of a place where you\'d find the rat pack drinking back in the day. If you\'re up for a ghost story just ask a bell boy.','2009-03-06 16:16:37',7,65),(318,'This unassuming spa in the deep NorthWest neighborhood of Portland delivers the goods!  when we finally found the place i was a little concerned that it wasn\'t going to be luxurious enough.  some of the atmostphere is a little new-agey/hippie, but the more you get accustomed to it the more the professionalism and skill and care come forward.  the amenities are not over the top, but ample.  there\'s a sauna in the shower room, decent robes, a sanctuary for between sessions.  we started with a foot soak on plush sofas with amazing tea and relaxation sank in.  then i had a foot massage by a deft woman with strong hands.  then my first ever facial which was decadent and great.  finished off with an amazing full body massage.  every person we came in contact with was top notch.  i recommend this place highly if you\'re looking for a serious spa getaway.','2009-03-09 10:24:13',2,65),(319,'There\'s not a lot of buzz about this place and the online reviews are mixed, but my first trip here the other night made me think this place could go in the rotation.  it may have been a fluke, but i will go back to find out.  first of all the service was friendly and thorough and attentive.  a must for a restaurant striving for this caliber.  the starters, at quick glance, don\'t jump at you, but linger.  there is treasure to be found in there.  the chickpea fries, the warm olives, the carrots, and on and on.  Meriwethers runs its own farm and the menu is ever-changing and fresh.  the pasta dish i had was great while the risoto was fine but nothing special.  a great atmosphere and cocktail menu just add to the experience.  there are also foodie events; the last sunday supper looks especially interesting: the chef cooks everything in the hearth with a collection of old ironware.  highly recommended.','2009-03-09 10:38:31',2,65),(321,'the best bet for this place is to get a sampling of smaller plates that way you can try everything. The chick pea fries are not to be missed. Ambiance is cozy and the staff is at the ready. It\'s a must try.','2009-03-09 10:47:11',7,65),(328,'This little artisan pizza gem hidden on a side street in the Richmond is a find and a half.  the pizza here is incredibly good.  all artisan pizza wants to be this.  the place is tiny, so good luck getting a seat.  once you\'re in you\'ll feel like you\'re part of something special.','2009-03-18 13:06:14',2,65),(334,'The upper east side has a surprising little secret: the sushi is pretty good. Poke is one of the reasons why. This non-assuming sushi bar serves up the goods and the sashimi is super fresh. If you want a little drink with your food bring a bottle of wine, they\\\'ll uncork it for you.  I hear its crowded often, but I went on a Monday night and did just find getting a seat with a friend. There\\\'s also plenty of room at the Sushi bar if you want to be close to the action.','2009-03-26 15:11:25',7,65),(349,'I tried it last night and really dug the ambience. The food was interesting and good. Lots of local fresh ingredients. Since there are smaller portions of the main dishes you can share a few and a get a rea