 ','2009-08-12 09:11:23',5,65),(416,'This is somewhere Frank Sinatra et al. would be comfortable.  Nice big plush booths of wine-color, waiters in black tie.  Food is decadent and tasty.  Great service.  There\\\'s a good happy hour and the bar is a great place to eat on a crowded night.','2009-09-09 14:19:54',2,65),(423,'This is mostly a placeholder while i wait for Joni\\\'s review.  she\\\'s more of a spa pro than i.  i\\\'d have to say for me this was really good, but not the pinnacle.  like the rest of the resort, incredible service and competence.  i just felt the design of the area was not quite spot on..','2009-11-10 11:59:33',2,65),(424,'The Jory restaurant and bar are both high-end yet lacking in some je ne sais quoi.  It might be the fact that the bar is hidden from view when you first enter from the lobby, which for someone like me puts one at unease.  once found, the bar is perfectly useable.  The bartender this evening, like all the hotel staff, was fully competent.  No false moves.  I can\\\'t tell you how important that is in staff.  Ge made a fine gin martini.  At first the bar and the seating area feel too detached, but it quickly grows comfortable.  \r\n\r\nThis night there was a two-piece backing up a sexy lounge singer.  The mood was good, but not energetic.  There\\\'s a lot of potential here, and the place is still basically a blank slate with only being open two months.  They can mold a clientelle into something special.  I yearn for high-end patronage when i pay this kind of loot.  not the kid with his incessant iPhone distraction next to me at one point.\r\n\r\nThe restaurant, too, just has a funky layout.  This whole hotel is about strange, yet working, layouts.  Seating was comfortable and intimate enough.  The only hiccup for our whole stay was the time between being seated and having our drink order taken.  Other than that there was never a want for anything.  The food here was middling.  Not quite to the level of top kitchen, but incredibly adequate.  the pork chop was better than the trout.  the squash soup was awesome, the ragout very tasty.  \r\n\r\nWe left happy and felt like dinner was paced right for the restaurant.  I think in the future i would like to sit at the counter with a view of the theatre kitchen.  As long as you sit far enough from the worker ants it would be fun if the staff in the kitchen were outgoing.','2009-11-10 12:23:35',2,65),(16,'hard to say now.  ownership has changed hands and i haven\'t been back since. ','2008-10-29 23:33:04',2,62),(35,'Great staff keeps this place in rotation.  Passable breakfast without a wait.  Sometimes you want to go where everybody knows your name.  Romand and Grant and Jason are some of the best industry folks in the city.  Monday night is Rock \'n\' Roll Trivia Nite hosted by yours truly.  -- EDITORS NOTE: all has changed.  no smoking, no good service, ownership chanes 4x over, bad food, loss of character.  not feeling it anymore, def. out of rotation.','2009-03-11 17:33:33',2,62),(192,'reviews online make it sound like a classic spot -- both positive and negative.  league every night till 9:15, but open lanes mondays','2008-10-16 12:23:08',2,62),(197,'league till about 9:30 on wednesdays, then it\'s a ghost house.  service with a frown.  with 47 open lanes they put a screaming, albeit ghetto-fabulous, family right next to us.  russian-mafia vibe.\r\n','2008-10-16 12:30:38',2,62),(333,'The service and the food leave little to be desired. We were rushed through our meal at 6:00 on Sunday and the restaurant was half empty. I\\\'ve been to ShunLee East and it\\\'s far superior. Go there instead or even the cafe, which has a slightly different menu, but still plenty of choices. It was a true disappointment. Don\\\'t waste your time.','2009-03-26 15:05:38',7,62),(342,'affectionately dubbed the dirtbag bar by the group of cororkers who choose this destination for 2 reasons: dirt cheap and across the street from work.  it\\\'s a drity feeling bar w