ry','2009-05-19 13:57:12',2,NULL),(364,'to try','2009-05-19 14:12:08',2,NULL),(368,'to try','2009-05-26 15:22:23',2,NULL),(369,'to try','2009-05-26 15:23:22',2,NULL),(370,'to try','2009-05-26 15:24:12',2,NULL),(371,'i want to LOVE Izakaya, i really do.  but i don\'t think i do.  i mean, we tried this place last night, and although i could tell everything was fantastically prepared, the true example of real izakaya, i just wasn\'t that wowed.  and at the prices there, i would think twice before going back.  i should say that we went on a sunday and that on sundays sushi is not available, but i wasn\'t there for sushi.  i wanted the izakaya experience.  the next big food fad, izakaya is even fun to say.  it\'s japanese, well, small plate.  some of the earthy tastes remind me of Korean side dishes.  some pickling here, some some there.  \r\n\r\nthe service was fine, but the atmosphere was slightly lacking.  this did not feel like the place Anthony Bourdain had drunkenly displayed on his TV show.  i will definitely grab any opportunity to eat sushi here, but i\'ll stick with Portland for Izakaya for now.  Portland beat SF to hipping this cuisine, and so far it does a better job.','2010-06-07 16:45:22',2,64),(372,'veg','2009-05-26 15:27:01',2,NULL),(391,'gotta finally get to this place; good outdoors','2009-06-23 11:40:02',2,NULL),(392,'this place looked like it had a lot of potential during the build-out.  it never quite got there, but since it\\\'s been a while i should go revisit the place.  it has a good outdoor area.','2009-06-23 11:42:05',2,NULL),(412,'Great experience.  The cocktails were inventive and the food was great.  Good local, organic ingredients and for an amazing price.  Go there.','2009-08-21 23:26:17',6,NULL),(413,'Creative cocktails from a knowledgeable and friendly bartender/owner.  Food = tasty Mediterranean appetizers, but if you are here walk down the street to The Observatory for dinner.','2009-08-21 23:28:39',6,NULL),(415,'Place is pretty pedest