ted to buy two.  Don\'t.  With the healthy portion of damn-near-perfect fries (drizzled with the right amount of truffle oil, unlinke their Little Bird fry counterpart.  And they have a root beer float.  and hipster beer.  the food\'s great.  i wouldn\'t wait for it.  and the fries might be the best in town.  definitely worth checking out.  Just skip the lunch rush and enjoy it when it\'s not a douchebag purse.','2011-02-09 12:16:07',2,64),(2043,'I\'ve only been here for a House Spirits RPM, but the place had great atmosphere. Will definitely come back to try out the food. I appreciate the french affect the servers work hard on. It\'s like an upscale alternative for Montage. The bar is huge and they respect the cocktail. More after attendance. ','2011-02-19 12:45:19',2,65),(2044,'I\'m not sure how the dude with the trucker hat and mustache can maintain that snarl in the midst of this mediocrity. Wait, I think I answered my own question. This new, hip pizza joint could almost be confused for a pop up with the uninspired use of cheap building materials as style. Needless to say, this place could do great with this kind of crowd. \r\n\r\nThe prices follow the trend upward like all new places opening in this down economy. But people flock so who can blame them. My pizza: just alright. Dry and mouth scraping crust with too little sauce. ','2011-03-02 19:58:00',2,64),(2045,'Finally catching on with the in crowd, it looks like the newest incarnation of this location may stick around a while. A good thing. \r\n\r\nFriendly staff; they really do your name. Great pizza and other foods. Limited cocktail menu.  They are not staffed for speed, it\'s more bistro/cafe than bar. \r\n\r\nThe interior was remodeled a while back and is an unexpected treat.','2011-03-02 21:09:27',2,65),(2046,'Wish list','2011-03-13 13:31:20',2,62),(2047,'Wish list','2011-03-13 13:31:22',2,62),(2048,'Unassuming find near pcc. Shit tons of beer. Package store. Snacks. People feel hip here. ','2011-03-31 16:12:03',2,65),(2049,'Come for the view, stay for the... well, then just leave; the food is bad. Good service and lot\'s of happy tourists. Please exit through the gift shop. ','2011-04-26 14:27:05',8,63),(2050,'This may very well be the best food in Newport. Friendly mamason and papason, situated on a janky dock over the bay. In a neighborhood of overpriced seafood joints and tourist traps, this place is the right stuff. ','2011-04-26 19:28:14',8,66),(2051,'Holy fucking shit does this awesome bartender swear like a fucking sailor. We call him Sailor Harley. It\'ll make sense. If you\'re on the bay front and need a drink this is as good as any. ','2011-06-18 13:17:04',2,64),(527,'This is a decent sushi joint in the cuts.  Not the most up-to-date decor, but the service and food will uplift that.','2011-03-16 12:21:02',2,64),(528,'I\'ve been wanting to try Wylie Dufresne food ever since I saw him on Top Chef Masters. I wanted to know if tiny food deconstructed was any good or even filling. Good news: It was on both counts. I didn\'t get to try a lot there, but what I did eat was amazing. I, of course, had to give the eggs benedict a try since that\'s a signature desk, but the other appetizer I ate was phenomenal - a duck, with horseradish, purple mustard, and baby celery. Yes, there is such a thing. The cocktails were excellent as well. \r\n\r\nOne of my favorite things about WD-50 is the atmosphere. The staff couldn\'t be more friendly or welcoming. Everyone seemed to take delight at how everyone felt about the food they were eating. I can\'t wait to go back for a full meal. As for the prices, it\'s not cheap, but by NY standards it\'s definitely fair.','2011-03-25 11:35:25',7,66),(529,'we decided to go here after finding Chez Jose east had closed  :)  Too bad, because IMO there is a paucity of \'go to\' Mexican place in Portland.  Overall, the OTH was OK. I had the tilapia tacos. . .pretty good. Good chips and salsa too. The Margaritas however were not that good. . .they used a mix and then did not give it a good shake. Stick to the house margarita, as they probably don\'t have enough experience preparing the premium drinks. The guacamole was off as well. They ostensibly mix avocado and sour cream together and the resulting color is less than appetizing. All of that said though this is a good , kid friendly spot when in a pinch. Not the best Mexican food in town, but a friendly place and given they have been open since 1960, a Portland institution.','2011-04-05 14:10:22',15,NULL),(530,'Izzy\'s Steaks may be located in a strip mall, but once you go inside you\'re transported to another place and time especially if you head into the bar. You\'ll easily feel like you could be at one of Frank Sinatra\'s old haunts. It has a piano player, well done mood lighting and a solid bar that occupies most of the room. There\'s still room for other seating options as well if you\'re with a larger party. As big as the bar is it never gets too loud so you can still have intimate conversations. \r\n\r\nThe food is delicious as well and the portions are big. So if you\'re not a big eater plan on sharing. The sides are probably my favorite, cooked exactly as you would find in just about any famous steak house.','2011-05-27 12:21:05',7,65),(531,'Right across from the dirtbaggiest of the dirtbag parks -- O\'Bryant Square -- lies this great little find.  They\'ve sort of got their marketing down for a cart, but that shouldn\'t turn you off.  They serve one dish (Mi Quang) which made the vendor and i both laugh when he caught himself.  They tout their dish as healthy vietnamese food and a little flyer that comes in your bag even tells you which herb is going to cure which ailment.\r\n\r\nThe healthy ingredients sure taste good.  and fresh.  the broth is tasty and you\'ve got all sorts of critters in their: chicken, pork, shrimp, quail egg.  the noodles are good, too.  this is worth 6 bucks.  i\'ll go back. though i might ask them to put in a second shrimp and quail egg like in the picture!','2011-06-20 13:21:45',2,65),(532,'Otto takes over a space that has a long pedigree: Ken\'s Plate, Sel Gris, Fin...  Now Otto.  And we were not disappointed.  They\'re doing the whole soft launch steelo but I was still surprised how empty it was.  At least they weren\'t slacking in the kitchen.  The three couples that were there got a great meal.  My escolar was perfectly cooked and seasoned and the cornmeal dumplings were out of this world.  The lamb oxtail was also incredible.\r\n\r\nBesides the food, the place has a nice casual, comfortable atmosphere and a great server.  I especially like the 8-top counter in the middle of the room for bigger parties or communal dining.  Make sure to go support this fantastic place.','2011-06-29 13:04:57',2,65),(533,'This tiny bomb bunker of a building at 55th and E B\'side may not look like much from the outside, but there\'s a lot going on inside.  Your best bet is to scare up about six friends, get a reservation, and just ask for one of everything on the menu.  Here, you\'ve got about 4 of those young, skinny, new-hippie types (pampered skin/clothes) dishing out small and entree plates of eclectic, local, tasty food.  bold flavor combinations, rich sauces, great color and texture.  It\'s a whole experience.  Didn\'t feel too trendy or spoiled yet, people were genuinely just in there to eat some good grub, not be seen.  No boozes  yet, but good wine and beer list.  ','2011-07-11 16:19:38',2,65),(2052,'Another new restaurant for division street.   Japanese/izakaya. We went to one of the opening nights and enjoyed the tasting menu. Good atmosphere, great ramen. ','2011-09-21 00:04:42',2,65);
